title: ESA reveals Euclid’s first five images
summary: The European Space Agency (ESA) has released the first full-color images from Euclid, the agency’s latest space telescope designed to study the nature and distribution of dark matter and dark energy in the universe. During a video broadcast on Nov. 7, scientists, engineers, and agency officials unveiled the telescope’s first five images.

title: SpaceX launches ninth dedicated rideshare mission
summary: SpaceX launched more than 100 satellites in the ninth in a series of dedicated smallsat rideshare missions Nov. 11, the latest flight in a program that has generated both delight and disdain across the commercial space industry.

title: SpaceX Transporter 9 rideshare features new OTV from Tom Mueller’s Impulse Space
summary: On Saturday, Nov. 11 SpaceX will launch the Transporter-9 rideshare mission from launch complex SLC-4E at Vandenberg Space Force Base (VSFB). The 55-minute launch window opens at 10:49 AM PST (18:49 UTC). If needed there is a backup launch opportunity the next day with the same launch window.

title: Transportation Department official suggests industry help pay for FAA commercial space office
summary: A top Department of Transportation official suggested the launch industry should help pay for additional resources for the Federal Aviation Administration’s commercial space office.

title: Avanti in LEO talks to become a multi-orbit connectivity provider
summary: Avanti Communications is in talks to procure capacity from a low Earth orbit operator to transform into a provider of multi-orbit broadband services, the British regional geostationary satellite operator announced Nov. 10.

title: Qualcomm ends partnership for connecting Android phones to Iridium satellites
summary: Semiconductor giant Qualcomm is scrapping plans to provide the technology Android smartphones would need to directly connect to Iridium’s satellites when they can’t reach a cell tower.

title: Ron Baron expects SpaceX’s Starlink to go public around 2027
summary: Billionaire investor Ron Baron told CNBC on Friday that he expects SpaceX to IPO its Starlink satellite internet service “in 2027 or so.”

title: NASA's Mars Fleet Will Still Conduct Science While Lying Low
summary: Rovers and orbiters will continue collecting limited data during a two-week communications pause due to the position of Earth, the Sun, and the Red Planet.
